4. BloodHound Useful Queries

BloodHound is used to identify privilege escalation paths.

Find Domain Admin paths
MATCH (u:User),(g:Group {name:"DOMAIN ADMINS@DOMAIN.LOCAL"}),p=shortestPath((u)-[*1..]->(g))
RETURN p
Find kerberoastable accounts
MATCH (u:User {hasspn:true})
RETURN u
Find users with admin rights
MATCH (u:User)-[:AdminTo]->(c:Computer)
RETURN u,c
Find unconstrained delegation
MATCH (c:Computer {unconstraineddelegation:true})
RETURN c


